{"type":"message","id":"77dcb809","parentId":"d27e5789","timestamp":"2026-05-18T09:37:57.061Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01GwLBi9XPaP2cgqtWzJDPaz","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"11: Feishu/Lark is an all-in-one collaboration platform where teams chat, share documents, manage calendars, and get work done together.\r\n13: **Status:** production-ready for bot DMs + group chats. WebSocket is the default mode; webhook mode is optional.\r\n47: - `\"allowlist\"` — only users listed in `allowFrom` can chat (default: bot owner only)\r\n48: - `\"open\"` — allow public DMs only when `allowFrom` includes `\"*\"`; with restrictive entries, only matching users can chat\r\n58: ### Group chats\r\n60: **Group policy** (`channels.feishu.groupPolicy`):\r\n64: | `\"open\"`      | Respond to all messages in groups                                                            |\r\n65: | `\"allowlist\"` | Only respond to groups in `groupAllowFrom` or explicitly configured under `groups.<chat_id>` |\r\n66: | `\"disabled\"`  | Disable all group messages; explicit `groups.<chat_id>` entries do not override this         |\r\n74: - Per-group override: `channels.feishu.groups.<chat_id>.requireMention`\r\n79: ## Group configuration examples\r\n81: ### Allow all groups, no @mention required\r\n87:       groupPolicy: \"open\",\r\n93: ### Allow all groups, still require @mention\r\n99:       groupPolicy: \"open\",\r\n106: ### Allow specific groups only\r\n112:       groupPolicy: \"allowlist\",\r\n113:       // Group IDs look like: oc_xxx\r\n114:       groupAllowFrom: [\"oc_xxx\", \"oc_yyy\"],\r\n120: In `allowlist` mode, you can also admit a group by adding an explicit `groups.<chat_id>` entry. Explicit entries do not override `groupPolicy: \"disabled\"`. Wildcard defaults under `groups.*` configure matching groups, but they do not admit groups by themselves."}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":191,"aggregated":"11: Feishu/Lark is an all-in-one collaboration platform where teams chat, share documents, manage calendars, and get work done together.\r\n13: **Status:** production-ready for bot DMs + group chats. WebSocket is the default mode; webhook mode is optional.\r\n47: - `\"allowlist\"` — only users listed in `allowFrom` can chat (default: bot owner only)\r\n48: - `\"open\"` — allow public DMs only when `allowFrom` includes `\"*\"`; with restrictive entries, only matching users can chat\r\n58: ### Group chats\r\n60: **Group policy** (`channels.feishu.groupPolicy`):\r\n64: | `\"open\"`      | Respond to all messages in groups                                                            |\r\n65: | `\"allowlist\"` | Only respond to groups in `groupAllowFrom` or explicitly configured under `groups.<chat_id>` |\r\n66: | `\"disabled\"`  | Disable all group messages; explicit `groups.<chat_id>` entries do not override this         |\r\n74: - Per-group override: `channels.feishu.groups.<chat_id>.requireMention`\r\n79: ## Group configuration examples\r\n81: ### Allow all groups, no @mention required\r\n87:       groupPolicy: \"open\",\r\n93: ### Allow all groups, still require @mention\r\n99:       groupPolicy: \"open\",\r\n106: ### Allow specific groups only\r\n112:       groupPolicy: \"allowlist\",\r\n113:       // Group IDs look like: oc_xxx\r\n114:       groupAllowFrom: [\"oc_xxx\", \"oc_yyy\"],\r\n120: In `allowlist` mode, you can also admit a group by adding an explicit `groups.<chat_id>` entry. Explicit entries do not override `groupPolicy: \"disabled\"`. Wildcard defaults under `groups.*` configure matching groups, but they do not admit groups by themselves.","cwd":"C:\\Users\\yyzypublic\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1779097077060}}
